<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="1114" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="13.[813,1420,1683,2091]" pageId="13" pageNumber="1114">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[850,961,1863,1887]" pageId="13" pageNumber="1114">Remarks.</emphasis>
This taxon was treated as two distinct species: Afrotropical 
<taxonomicName authority="Zilli (2000)" authorityName="Zilli" authorityYear="2000" box="[1040,1299,1897,1921]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Mocis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="1114" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="proverai">
<emphasis box="[1040,1166,1898,1921]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="1114">M. proverai</emphasis>
Zilli (2000)
</taxonomicName>
; Indo-Australian 
<taxonomicName box="[889,1008,1931,1955]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Mocis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="1114" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="frugalis">
<emphasis box="[889,1008,1931,1955]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="1114">M. frugalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and recognized the old concept of 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Mocis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="1114" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="frugalis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="1114">M. frugalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by Zilli (200b). The pale ochreous brown colour of both wings similar in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Cramer" baseAuthorityYear="1779" box="[1094,1321,1999,2023]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Trigonodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="1114" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hyppasia">
<emphasis box="[1094,1321,1999,2023]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="1114">Trigonodes hyppasia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
whereas lacking the black triangles. Male genitalia with uncus broad, harpe well developed.
</paragraph>
